cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.IR 

This paper deals with defending against label manipulation attacks in machine learning, specifically in the context of malware detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also proposes deep learning algorithms, which suggests a possible fit with cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed algorithms on different datasets and features, which could also fit with cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
